radiographic_examinations.findings: Inflamed, fluid-filled appendix surrounded by free fluid measuring up to 11 mm in diameter; 13 mm appendicolith with a rim enhancing fluid collection distal to this, likely small contained rupture. No evidence of concerning focal lesions in liver, pancreas, spleen, and kidneys. Eccentric filling defect in the mid SMV concerning for nonocclusive SMV thrombus.
